---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Speaking & Collaboration | Jing Betty Feng"
  description="Jing Betty Feng is available for invited talks, panels, workshops, and academic collaboration in AI, global business, innovation, and workforce development."
>

  <!-- PAGE HERO -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-hero__label">Speaking &amp; Collaboration</p>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">Engaged Scholarship Beyond the University</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__intro">
        Betty welcomes invitations for talks, workshops, panels, and
        interdisciplinary partnerships with academic, organizational,
        and community audiences.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- INTRO -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="speaking-intro-heading">
    <div class="container container--prose">
      <p class="section-label">Invitation</p>
      <h2 id="speaking-intro-heading">Open to Collaboration</h2>
      <div class="section-divider"></div>
      <p>
        Betty believes that academic work is enriched by engagement with
        practitioners, community leaders, and interdisciplinary collaborators.
        She is actively open to speaking invitations, workshop facilitation,
        panel participation, and collaboration on curriculum and program development.
      </p>
      <p>
        Her presentations are grounded in peer-reviewed scholarship and
        informed by years of organizational experience — making them
        accessible and credible to both academic and professional audiences.
        She brings the same care to an invited lecture as to a published paper:
        rigor in the ideas, clarity in the delivery.
      </p>
      <div style="margin-top:var(--space-8);">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary">Inquire About Collaboration</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SPEAKING TOPICS -->
  <section class="section section--alt" aria-labelledby="topics-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header--center">
        <p class="section-label">Areas of Expertise</p>
        <h2 id="topics-heading">Speaking Topics</h2>
        <p class="section-intro text-center" style="margin-inline:auto;">
          Betty speaks from a position of scholarly credibility and practical experience.
          Topics can be adapted for academic, professional, and interdisciplinary audiences.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-2">
        <div class="topic-card">
          <div class="topic-card__icon">🤖</div>
          <h3 class="topic-card__title">AI Literacy and Business Education</h3>
          <p class="topic-card__body">
            What does it mean to educate business leaders for an AI-shaped world?
            Betty speaks on AI literacy frameworks, responsible adoption, curriculum
            design, and the human dimensions of AI in organizational settings.
          </p>
          <div class="topic-card__tags">
            <span class="tag">Universities</span>
            <span class="tag">Business Schools</span>
            <span class="tag">Workforce Programs</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <div class="topic-card__icon">🌐</div>
          <h3 class="topic-card__title">International Business and Cross-Cultural Leadership</h3>
          <p class="topic-card__body">
            Drawing on scholarship and direct experience in multinational firms,
            Betty speaks on cultural dynamics in global organizations, cross-cultural
            negotiation, and the challenges of leading across national boundaries.
          </p>
          <div class="topic-card__tags">
            <span class="tag">Academic Conferences</span>
            <span class="tag">Business Leaders</span>
            <span class="tag">MBA Programs</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <div class="topic-card__icon">💡</div>
          <h3 class="topic-card__title">Innovation, Entrepreneurship, and Experiential Learning</h3>
          <p class="topic-card__body">
            How do we design learning experiences that genuinely develop entrepreneurial
            capability? Betty speaks on innovation pedagogy, design thinking, the
            Innovation Challenge, and the evidence base for experiential education.
          </p>
          <div class="topic-card__tags">
            <span class="tag">Educators</span>
            <span class="tag">Accreditors</span>
            <span class="tag">Student Audiences</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <div class="topic-card__icon">🌱</div>
          <h3 class="topic-card__title">Sustainability, Workforce, and Regional Development</h3>
          <p class="topic-card__body">
            Betty speaks on workforce transitions in support of a more sustainable future, with particular attention to regional economic development, circular economy, MWBE enterprise development, and community-engaged professional development.
          </p>
          <div class="topic-card__tags">
            <span class="tag">Workforce Organizations</span>
            <span class="tag">Community Partners</span>
            <span class="tag">Policy Audiences</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <div class="topic-card__icon">🧭</div>
          <h3 class="topic-card__title">Human-Centered Adoption of Emerging Technologies</h3>
          <p class="topic-card__body">
            Technology adoption succeeds or fails based on the human and
            organizational factors surrounding it. Betty speaks on how organizations
            can center human needs, ethical reasoning, and learning capacity
            in their approach to emerging technology.
          </p>
          <div class="topic-card__tags">
            <span class="tag">Organizations</span>
            <span class="tag">HR &amp; L&amp;D</span>
            <span class="tag">Cross-Sector Audiences</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <div class="topic-card__icon">🎓</div>
          <h3 class="topic-card__title">The Scholar-Practitioner in Contemporary Business Education</h3>
          <p class="topic-card__body">
            What is the value of practical experience in academic work — and how does
            a scholar-practitioner identity shape research, teaching, and institutional
            contribution? A reflective talk for academic and pedagogical audiences.
          </p>
          <div class="topic-card__tags">
            <span class="tag">Faculty Development</span>
            <span class="tag">Academic Leadership</span>
            <span class="tag">Accreditation Panels</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FORMATS -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="formats-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header--center">
        <p class="section-label">Engagement Types</p>
        <h2 id="formats-heading">Formats</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="formats-grid">
        <div class="format-item">
          <h3>Keynote &amp; Invited Lecture</h3>
          <p>Full-length academic or professional keynote on any topic area, calibrated to the audience and occasion.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="format-item">
          <h3>Faculty Workshop</h3>
          <p>Facilitated professional development for academic colleagues — including pedagogy, curriculum design, and AI in teaching.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="format-item">
          <h3>Student Workshop</h3>
          <p>Interactive session for undergraduate or graduate students — on topics ranging from global business to AI careers and entrepreneurship.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="format-item">
          <h3>Panel Discussion</h3>
          <p>Panelist or moderator for academic conference panels, interdisciplinary symposia, and professional forums.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="format-item">
          <h3>Academic Conference Presentation</h3>
          <p>Formal paper or work-in-progress presentation at disciplinary conferences in international business, management education, and related fields.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="format-item">
          <h3>Cross-Sector Roundtable</h3>
          <p>Contributor to facilitated conversations between academic, government, industry, and community stakeholders on shared challenges.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- IDEAL AUDIENCES -->
  <section class="section section--alt" aria-labelledby="audiences-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header--center">
        <p class="section-label">Who Betty Speaks With</p>
        <h2 id="audiences-heading">Ideal Audiences</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="audiences-grid">
        <div class="audience-item">
          <h3>Universities and Business Schools</h3>
          <p>Academic colleagues, administrative leaders, faculty development programs, and student audiences at accredited institutions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-item">
          <h3>Academic Associations</h3>
          <p>AIB, AoM, and related disciplinary associations in international business, management education, and organizational behavior.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-item">
          <h3>Workforce and Community Organizations</h3>
          <p>Regional organizations focused on workforce development, economic inclusion, sustainability transitions, and adult education.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-item">
          <h3>Mission-Driven Organizations</h3>
          <p>Nonprofits, public agencies, and social enterprises working at the intersection of business, learning, and community impact.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-item">
          <h3>Interdisciplinary Audiences</h3>
          <p>Symposia and events that bring together scholars, practitioners, and community voices around shared challenges.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COLLABORATION CTA -->
  <section class="section section--dark" aria-labelledby="collab-cta-heading">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <p class="section-label section-label--light">Reach Out</p>
      <h2 id="collab-cta-heading" style="color:#fff;margin-bottom:var(--space-4);">
        Interested in Working Together?
      </h2>
      <p class="section-intro section-intro--light" style="margin-inline:auto;margin-bottom:var(--space-8);">
        Please include your organization, the nature of the invitation or collaboration,
        and any relevant timeline. Betty reviews all inquiries personally.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--outline-light">Inquire About Collaboration</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* Topic cards */
  .topic-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }
  .topic-card__icon { font-size: 2rem; }
  .topic-card__title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .topic-card__body {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
    flex: 1;
  }
  .topic-card__tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    margin-top: auto;
  }

  /* Formats */
  .formats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  @media (max-width: 860px) { .formats-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
  @media (max-width: 500px) { .formats-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .format-item {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
  }
  .format-item h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .format-item p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }

  /* Audiences */
  .audiences-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  @media (max-width: 860px) { .audiences-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
  @media (max-width: 500px) { .audiences-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .audience-item {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }
  .audience-item h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .audience-item p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }
</style>
